export default DailyTransactions;

To fix the issue where the scanner opens but fails to read the specific barcode (`54660-B4000`), I will simplify the scanner implementation to ensure maximum compatibility and scan area.

**The Fix:**
1.  **Full Frame Scanning:** I will remove the `qrbox` configuration passed to the scanner. This forces the scanner to analyze the **entire camera frame** instead of just a small box. This is crucial for long 1D barcodes which often get clipped by the software crop box. I will still keep the visual box for user guidance.
2.  **High Resolution:** I will enforce high-resolution video constraints (`1920x1080`) to ensure the thin bars of the barcode are distinguishable.
3.  **Standard Library:** I will revert to using the standard `html5-qrcode` library implementation (which handles device abstraction well) but enable its experimental native support flag. This is often more stable than a custom native implementation.

